title: New Garden Center Gardheimar soon to be opened in Reykjavik
content:
Exciting news for garden enthusiasts in Iceland's capital Reykjavik! A new state-of-the-art garden center is in the works, promising to offer the best gardening experience in the country. The team behind this project is currently working on several aspects, including building design, routing design, assortment selection, 3D rendering, and close cooperation with suppliers to ensure the best possible selection of plants, tools, and other gardening supplies.
![Page Image 0](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/poster-1.jpg)


The garden center's building design is a crucial aspect of the project. The goal is to create a space that is both functional and aesthetically pleasing, with plenty of natural light and ventilation. The building will be designed to allow for a seamless flow of customers throughout the center, with ample space for browsing and selecting plants and other gardening supplies. The center will be fully equipped with modern facilities, including a coffee shop, a children's play area, and ample parking space.

Routing design is another important aspect of the project. The goal is to create a logical and easy-to-navigate layout that will make shopping at the garden center a stress-free and enjoyable experience. The routing design will take into account the different types of plants and gardening supplies available, and the best way to display them to customers.

Assortment selection is a critical aspect of the garden center. The team is working closely with suppliers to ensure a wide selection of high-quality plants, including both native Icelandic species and exotic plants from around the world. Additionally, the center will offer a vast selection of gardening tools, accessories, and other supplies, making it a one-stop-shop for all gardening needs.

Rendering 3D models of the garden center is another essential aspect of the project. This allows the team to visualize the space and make any necessary changes before construction begins. The 3D models will help ensure that the final product is exactly what the team envisions, creating an exceptional and unique experience for customers.

Finally, the team is working closely with suppliers to create the best garden center at the planet. This includes selecting the best plants and products for the center, as well as ensuring that everything is of the highest quality. The team is committed to creating a green garden center that will not only provide customers with excellent gardening supplies but also contribute to a sustainable future.

In conclusion, the new garden center in Reykjavik is set to be a game-changer for garden enthusiasts in Iceland. The team is working tirelessly to ensure that every aspect of the center is of the highest quality, from the building design to the assortment selection. Customers can look forward to a unique and enjoyable shopping experience, with an extensive selection of plants, gardening tools, and other supplies. The team is committed to creating the best garden center at the planet, and we can't wait to see the final product.

title: Greenconcetors works for edenparks on the development of a biophilic building
content:
GREENCONCEPTORS WORKES ON A BIOPHILIC BUILDING
![Page Image 0](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/600x0/planon_1_3--photo_1.jpg)


The development of the glass structure that connects two office buildings of the Planon head office is going well. The glass construction with a gutter height of 8 meters is used as a workplace, recreation room and showcase for their products. The buildingh will be used as a space for the employees to work in a natural surrounding connected with nature. The glashouse construction is cooled by solar panels on the roof and natural shading by trees. The biophilic builinding is connected to nature as much as possible.

title: Rooftop Garden Ebben Inspyrium starts blooming
content:
Maintaining a sustainable rooftop garden requires ongoing care and attention. Regular watering, pruning, and fertilizing are essential to ensure that the plants thrive. Additionally, monitoring the soil pH and nutrient levels can help to ensure that the plants receive the necessary nutrients to grow.

In conclusion, a sustainable rooftop garden is an excellent way to promote sustainability, increase biodiversity, and create a beautiful and functional outdoor space. By incorporating 3D printed benches, re-used materials, circularity, and native plants, a rooftop garden can become a self-sustaining ecosystem that thrives with minimal intervention. With the right design elements and ongoing care, a sustainable rooftop garden can be a source of beauty and inspiration for years to come. So, let's welcome the new season with open arms and a commitment to sustainability.


![Page Image 0](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/spring-is-coming-3.jpg)


## Rooftop Garden Ebben Inspyrium starts blooming
Tuesday April 25, 2023
## Rooftop Garden Ebben Inspyrium starts blooming

Spring is a season of renewal, growth, and vibrancy. As the weather starts to warm up, it's the perfect time to take advantage of rooftop gardens and make them into sustainable oases. With the right design elements and a commitment to using eco-friendly materials, a rooftop garden can become a beautiful and functional space that promotes sustainability and biodiversity.

One way to create a sustainable rooftop garden is by incorporating 3D printed benches. 3D printing is a technology that has been growing in popularity in recent years and can be used to create customized, durable, and eco-friendly pieces of furniture. When designing a rooftop garden, benches can be essential to provide seating areas, and using 3D printed benches can reduce waste and increase efficiency.


![Page Image 1](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/spring-is-coming-12.jpg)


Increasing biodiversity is another essential element of a sustainable rooftop garden. The use of native plants can attract local wildlife, such as bees and butterflies, which can help to pollinate the garden and increase biodiversity. A diverse range of plants can also help to regulate the microclimate, providing a cooling effect in the summer and insulation in the winter. Additionally, incorporating features such as bird feeders and nesting boxes can help to support local bird populations.
![Page Image 2](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/spring-is-coming-6.jpg)


Using re-used materials is another key element of a sustainable rooftop garden. From recycled wood to repurposed planters, there are countless ways to give new life to materials that would otherwise be discarded. Not only does this reduce waste, but it also adds character and uniqueness to the garden. Using reclaimed materials is also an affordable way to create a sustainable rooftop garden.

Circularity is a concept that is crucial for a sustainable rooftop garden. It's important to create a system where materials are used and reused in a continuous loop. This means choosing plants that can be easily composted, using rainwater harvesting systems, and creating a system where nutrients from the soil are returned to the garden. This way, the garden becomes a self-sustaining ecosystem that thrives with minimal intervention.
![Page Image 3](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/spring-is-coming-5.jpg)


When designing a sustainable rooftop garden, it's important to consider the local climate and weather conditions. The rooftop garden should be able to withstand the elements and thrive in the local environment. Choosing plants that are native to the area and can withstand the local weather conditions is a good way to ensure the success of the garden.

Another important consideration is the amount of sunlight that the rooftop garden will receive. Many plants require a certain amount of sunlight to grow, so it's important to choose plants that will thrive in the available light. Additionally, incorporating shading elements such as umbrellas or pergolas can help to protect plants from excessive sunlight.

Watering is another essential element of a rooftop garden. In order to conserve water and promote sustainability, it's important to use a drip irrigation system that delivers water directly to the roots of the plants. This can help to reduce water waste and ensure that the plants receive the necessary moisture to thrive. Additionally, rainwater harvesting systems can be used to collect and store rainwater for use in the garden.
![Page Image 4](https://www.greenconceptors.com/images/1000x0/spring-is-coming-11.jpg)

## GreenConceptors visits the World Expo 2020
Tuesday November 09, 2021

Finally it was possible to travel again to Dubai to visit the must see show World Expo 2020 in Dubai. Besides visiting our old relations we also were able to see the World largest exhibition that everybody is talking about.

From different countries presentations were made. Subjects like sustainability, greenwalls, solar energy, everything was presented at the exhibition. But also enviornment and new business opportunities for the different countries where displayed.

From Indonesia who says they are going to be the one of the largest economies in the year 2045 until jungles from Singapore were showed. All made in the hot burning sun but all with so much energy and positiveness that is was a pleasure to visit.

On the sustainability court, especially the booth from The Netherlands ;-) was very nice. With a waterfilter that caputurse water from warm air, so pure that you can drink it, to new technolosies that can connect people in a more efficient way.

New ideas, new energy and more and more green solutions.
